parseFrom

public int parseFrom(java.lang.String s,
                     int start)
              throws FBDataTypeException
Parses the receiver's content from the given String. Default is to invoke initialize() up to the first delimiter (comma, right parenthesis or right square bracket) after the given start position.

Parameters:
s - The String from which to parse the content.
start - The character position from which to begin parsing.
Returns:
The character position of the terminating delimiter.
Throws:
FBDataTypeException - NULL_OBJECT - The initialization String was null, INVALID_OBJECT - The String had invalid syntax or no terminator was found.
See Also:
NULL_OBJECT, FBDataTypeException.invalidObject(String)
